76561198008427902,Recommended,216890,20414419,"Posted: 8 January, 2016",all,Darth Marenghi,"Blood Bowl isn't for everyone, but if it's for you, you'll be completely sucked in by it.It's a turn based sports strategy game with a dark fantasy theme and an RPG leveling system. If you're still with me after that little description, then maybe Blood Bowl is for you.You start the game by selecting a team of bloodthirsty monsters from the Warhammer universe. Each race plays a little differently. The Orcs want to bash their opponents into the dirt. The Elves want to dodge around and make big passing plays. The Goblins have a bunch of dirty tricks up their sleeves. You choose your name, logo and colour and then you begin.The first time I played, I got completely thrashed by the computer. There is a learning curve present but there are plenty of guides online and a big community of players who can give you some pointers. Leveling up your guys in the right way is a big part of the game. Some skills like Block and Dodge are a must, other skills like Pass block are only used in specific circumstances and best saved for later.The sound is satisfying. The commentators are hilarious. I though the graphics were fine. It's an older game from a smaller studio, so I wasn't expecting much. There is a nice variety of units in the game. The Chaos Edition comes with 23 teams and there is plenty of single player content here to play around with if you want to avoid the highly competitive online scene. Some guys have been playing the board game since the 80s and will mop the floor with newer players.I'm loving Blood Bowl so far. Anyways, I've got to get back to trying to take my team ""The New Ork Ragerz"" to the Blood Bowl final."
