76561198063941776,Not Recommended,216890,18851451,"Posted: 2 November, 2015",all,Trinket,"This game... ohhhh this game... It is actually with a very heavy heart that I can actually give it a thumbs down. I am torn and seriously torn at this. I have had a lot of great moments, but a lot of bad moments as well. The problem with this game is in its entire appeal to RNJesus. If you love dice rolling games with a twist of strategy, then this is for you. If you are a diehard strategy nerd, then this game will leave you bitter when the opposing team kills 2 of your star players and then procedes to dodge the rest of your team into a touch down after 3 turns of you rolling 2 attacker downs.The temple of RNG is that of a 6 sided die where 1s are always failures and 6s are always successes. You can stack it in your favor where 2-6 is a success or a 6 is the only success, but you must realize that means there is always a possibility of 17% failure. To me, this is the deal breaker. This to me, breaks the game. This is akin to munchkin(a fine game in certain lights) which can be fun light-heartedly, but if I were to rank this game amongst other strategy games, it has to get the thumbs down.This game does have many strategic aspects and so I thoroughly enjoy it for a Saturday sitdown, but the mental engagement is severally lacking. You can even tell since the AIs only ability to perform better is through just giving it more perks than you. This always leaves a fairly sour taste in my mouth, but I can usualy power through it if the game plays if engaging enough. This game play isn't.So for the TLDR crowd, if you want an RNG game that mimicks strategy, get this game. If you actually like strategy games, then this game is a no for me."
