76561198111844894,Recommended,216890,11293504,"Posted: 17 July, 2014",all,MobiusColon,"Blood Bowl is an excellent turn-based strategy game that can provide many hours of fun and exciting gameplay. There is a bit of a learning curve, but everything you put in to Blood Bowl, Blood Bowl returns many times over. Blood Bowl combines intracate and careful strategy with just enough of a random factor to make every game interesting; even between a first-time player and a seasoned veteran. In my experience, Blood Bowl also had one of the best, most devoted fan bases of any game available today. Blood Bowl can be a cruel mistress at times, but she'll always keep you coming back for more.Visually the game is pretty mediocre. The models and animations are simple and frequently recycled, and the UI leaves something to be desired. However, the thrill of Blood Bowl does not come from the graphics, and these issues are slowly but steadily being addressed and updated."
