,Recommended,216890,17993870,"Posted: 11 September, 2015",all,Ogulus The Indifferent,"7/10Blood Bowl is a fun, if frustrating, PC version of the classic table top game. If you enter it with the expectation that it will be funny and a catastrophy, then you'll probably have a good time. If you think it'll play like an actual ball game, then you'll probably hate it.The Run Down: There are two types of teams: teams that smash and teams that play ball well. My recommendation is to start with a team that smashes well, such as The Undead, Necromantic, or one of the Chaos/Nurgal/Khorne teams. Everything is done by D6 rolls, so you will fail constantly at everything. You'll fail at picking up a ball that your players surround, you'll fail at throwing a ball to a player two inches away, and you'll fail at smashing a player 1/4 your size and strength. Luckily, the other team fails at an equal rate. Even on ""Easy"" this game is challenging. I picked this up in that massive developer pack with Styx, and this is one of the few games in that huge pack that's worth anything at all.Try it out."
