,Recommended,216890,11561670,"Posted: 5 August, 2014",all,isador,"Blood Bowl. Oh you.A turn-based RTS game inspired by american football, but with fantasy races and extra violence. Want to see a game of Werewolves vs Orks? How about Elves vs Dwarves? Just another day in Bloodbowl.The game, like its tabletop equivalent, is centered entirely around six-sided die rolls to determine the results of actions. While many different strategies can be applied to win games (ranging from the ""long pass,"" the ""passing train,"" or ""KILL THEM ALL"") and you'll surely find one suited to your style. The factions are diverse and the differences between them are meaningful, leading to a fun experience where you'll want to try out every faction, just to see what it's like!That being said, the game is very unforgiving. On a six-sided die, you will roll a surprising amount of fails. While this is just a part of the game, it's can be quite frustrating to new players, and there is a definite learning curve that one has to get past before you can really appreciate the depth of the game. Another thing that can be quite frustrating is that players from your team (and the enemy team) can get injured, sometimes permanently, which in tournaments can be devastating. Still, it's all part of the game, and you'll surely learn to love it as i did!If you love turn-based RTS games, or have a macabre fantasy of ""what would football be like if it was extra violent?"" then this is definitely a ""must try."""
