,Recommended,216890,1422210,"Posted: 25 February, 2013",all,thorvindr,"Great engine, but still plenty of bugs. First of all, the replay feature is all but useless. You can't rewind or pause. All you can do is watch the match in real time. you can slow down and speed up a bit, but that's not that useful. Full control would be awesome; a pause button would make it a meaningful feature.You can change player names, apparently. You have to do it before you buy the player, you can never change it again, and you have to go into the player's detail screen. As far as I know, there is absolutely no reason to look at this screen before you buy a player, except that it's the only way to change the name. It'd be nice to just click on the name of the player I'm about to buy to get an input cursor. You know, like every other windows application ever.Dice are still broken. When it's one player vs. another, it's fair (if not well-randomized), but it seems that the die rolls in a single-player game take into account the difficulty level.Custom lineups don't save properly. As long as I stay within the same game, the lineup I saved doesn't go anywhere. As soon as I start a new game, it's gone. so there's really no point in using the feature, since you still need to take time to set your line every single game.♥♥♥♥♥♥poor tutorial. Seriously. The tutorial is cute and entertaining, but because it's cute and entertaining, it's not very informative and it takes forever to get through. Seriously, this is the worst in-game tutorial I've ever had the misfortune to sit through.This right-click/left-click♥♥♥♥♥♥has GOT to go. Just get rid of the right-click mechanism entirely. The game doesn't need to tell the difference between a ""move here"" click and a ""select this player"" click because you can only possibly mean one or the other, depending on where you actually click. I suppose this might make sense in a real-time game, but I've yet to encounter anyone who actual plays this game in realtime mode.I think it's great that when a ""new edition"" is released, they very graciously offer a deep discount to anyone who already owns the game. But come on. You're essentially releasing DLC and re-packaging the entire game with each content pack. So when I bought Chaos Edition, I had to download the entire game again, instead of just having to download a patch and a content pack. Can't you just release DLC and regular patches like everybody else does?A spectator mode would be great too. It would be nice to be able to watch a game as it happens and do commentary. There is officially a ""spectator mode,"" but you're not watching the game live. When you enter ""spectator mode,"" it just plays the game's replay from turn one.There are just so many things that everybody else does properly and this game fails at miserably.I love BloodBowl, and I love paying a one-time price to play it forever. I just wish we had some modern devs instead of these DOS-era non-conformists."
