,Recommended,216890,32573108,Posted: 19 June,all,Lord Commissar Vect,"OK Ok, This game receives lots of hate, mostly from 14 year olds who get ragey when they lose. Who cares if you lose? It's part of the fun of Blood Bowl is the RNG that does affect most actions. If you like Warhammer (or the universe associated with it) Buy this. If you like pretty brutal RNG (similar to Xcom's pretty rage-worthy RNG) then you're likely to like this, so get it. Like Online Play, incredibly fun but pretty much dead since Blood Bowl 2 released. Chaos edition has something like 23 teams and it is worth picking up on sale. It's honestly very fun and actually got me into the tabletop version that Games Workshop released around a year ago. Give this a go, and give it some patience and like me you may find yourself sinking more than a few hours into it.Or you know, you could just quit after one match and refund the game.Oh and, Blood Bowl 2 exists (like I previously mentioned) and has a much higher polish, nicer graphics and some pretty cool added elements, though is essentialy the same game with less races and higher requirements.Oh and for anyone who decides to get the game, treat every dice roll as if it will fail, prepare for it and you will generally do much better."
