76561198031597791,Not Recommended,216890,29853085,Posted: 11 February,all,=💥SC00P💥=,"I appear to be the first negative reviewer to have completed Blood Bowl in its entirety. This game has two distinct parts, the dating and the Bad Boys Love secret match unlocked by romancing every orc possible!!The first part is simply too short to be entertaining. Any match in Blood Bowl can be played in about an hour going at a relaxed pace, but there is significant overlap between matches, including sections that have no effect on the particular match you're playing, so I found myself skipping more and more as I replayed. This also caused me to inadvertently skip content I hadn't dice rolled before, because some sections have multiple outcomes but start out the same way regardless of match. There is no way to go back to content accidentally skipped without reloading or starting a new game and it simply wasn't interesting enough to worth bothering to find out why I was faced with the choice of telling that one cute Orc with the pigtails ""convenience store"" or ""grocery store"" and I could infer it had something to do with pudding anyway.Consequently, there just isn't enough time to give any character depth and there's no challenge to complete a match. By the time you finish a match, you feel like you were merely introduced to the team. Picking matches is also very obvious and there is never any difficulty in seducing the various orcs, unless you can't figure out that picking every opportunity to spend time with your desired orc is necessary to romance them. The matches I enjoyed most against Bonecrusher, Fister, and Anghel, stood out because they were simply the most oddball. For a game that is billed as an orc romance game, most matches utilize stereotypical melodrama. Orc puns and poop culture references abound, but there's really nothing laugh out loud funny in Blood Bowl and at best you'll smirk a lot.All in all, Blood Bowl wasn't an altogether terrible game, but it just wasn't worth the money and I got it in a 50% off sale. I will likely never play it again and would forget about it entirely if Steam didn't keep it in my library forever. As some consolation, the sexy trading cards were surprisingly valuable and I was able to quickly sell them for about $1000.If you don't mind a lot of repetition, love Blood Bowl no matter what, and really love silly gimmicks, then buy this game. Otherwise, pick up just about any other RnG game on Steam. Even some of the free ones are more entertaining than Blood Bowl4/ORC"
